title: For Sale/Trade:  Saiga 12 Gauge w/ Quad Rails , New Stock, Grip, 10 round Mag
postcontent:
I am considering selling or trading my Saiga 12 Gauge if the right offer comes around. If you know about the Saiga then you know how cool this weapon is. If not, I will give you a brief rundown. 

The Saiga 12 is a hybrid of a 12 gauge shotgun and an AK 47. This shotgun is made for battle and nothing less. I bought the gun new 3 months ago and I have been slowly converting it from its sporter configuration into the monster that you see. 

I have added:

- UTG tactical quad rail. This comes with the long and short top rail and rubber rail covers.

- Gunfixers low brass kit: A 5 stage adjustable gas adjuster and new plug and spring. This changes the stock 2 setting plug to 5 settings to adjust the amount of gas. This allows you to shoot low brass cheap rounds and bird shot. 

- AGP 10 round extended magazine. Also comes with 5 round mag.

- A red dot / laser site (not the one in the picture).

- Tapco T6 adjustable stock (dark earth)

- Tapco forgrip (dark earth)

- Case

I also have a bunch of ammo for it, Winchester PDX1, Brenneke KO slugs, Winchester rifled hollow point slugs, and others. 

Not only is this gun an absolute monster of destruction, it also looks the part. This can be a good an bad thing, this gun is one of the most intimidating looking guns at the range and it draws a crowd. It is for this reason that I have decided that I have to sell this through a FFL dealer. I don't want anything on my conscience if the wrong person gets their hands on it. I know an FFL doesn't guarantee anything but my hopes is that this will at least keep gangbangers from contacting me. 

I have about $1400 invested in this gun, and I work on a budget. There are still a couple things I would like to do to it. There is a trigger modification that is popular, its not needed but some people like it. If I don't sell it, I will be doing the this mod to better balance the gun. 

I am sure I will take the money and buy another gun so I am also open to interesting trades. 

If you want any information or have a trade or offer, feel free to get in touch.

title: For Sale:  CZ-52 (Czechoslovakian military)
postcontent:
The CZ 52 (also known by the Czechoslovakian military designations vz. 52, for "model of 1952". is a semi-automatic pistol designed by two brothers, Jan and Jaroslav Kratochvíl, in the early 1950s for the Czechoslovakian military. Around 200,000 vz. 52s were made by Ceská Zbrojovka in Strakonice from 1952 to 1954. The vz. 52 replaced the 7.65 mm Browning caliber (.32 ACP) Vz.50, which had acquired a reputation for unreliability and was underpowered for its role as a military service sidearm. After 30 years of military service, the vz. 52 was replaced by the 9x18mm Makarov caliber . Cz-USA began importation into the US market in January of 1998 with the designation CZ 52
